title.narrative: COMMUNITY BASED CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: Community-based child protection, psychosocial, and reintegration services are available for vulnerable boys and girls, including survivors of all forms of violence, children with disabilities, children on the move and children associated with armed conflict in targeted municipalities., which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas (Covid), Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 girls and boys are better protected from violence, abuse and exploitation

description.narrative: UNICEF and partners continued to strengthen the protective environment for children at the community level. UNICEF focused on reaching the most vulnerable girls and boys (including Libyans, migrants, refugees and IDPs) with child protection services, including case management, specialized psychosocial support, and gender-based violence interventions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/04/2022
